<br>
Alot of people consider ac as being some sort of barrior rating given by the armor you are wearing. This isn't what it's normally mean for. It's supposed to be sort of the catch-all for all those combat manuevers that you don't want to have a skill check on. For instance, the ac in a monk's mystical headband somehow allows them to avoid being hit whereas the magical plate turns blows when they land...<br>
<br>
Therefore, a warrior having better mitigation than the same plate wearing knight is explainable in that ac doesnt have a direct correllation as to whether you will take damage or how much of it...it's a combination.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  thought it was obvious, i guess not. everquest is NOT a roleplaying game, trying to pretend it is in any kind of class balancing thread is stupid. anyways, if you want a roleplay reason... warriors would be better than anybody else, even other plate classes at taking damage because it IS what we do. constantly, warriors are getting beat on by everything from frogs to skeletons... we should learn to take a hit better.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't agree with this statement. There may not be alot of rp on your server, but EQ is a rp game and as such is based on the rpg's that came before it. The majority of servers do not have players that roleplay a majority of the time. The character classes are based on those originally cooked up by the D&amp;D boys down to the types of armor they can wear, the spells they can cast and the skills they have. The game strays in many instances, but D&amp;D was never meant to be played by 100k people at the same time with an average of 5k of them all able to interract at the same time.<br>
<br>
The warrior class should have the most hp, be able to take the most damage, and deal out the most melee damage (specialist classes like rogue and monk not withstanding). The reasoning this has always been true is that the warrior class doesn't do anything other than fight...that's it. The hybrid classes always had other bells and whistles and as such had penalties associated with those extras.<br>
<br>
With regard to the xp penalty, this was removed during the same patch that put knights on the same damage table as warriors. Feel free to look it up.<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
