Dure to quotes and attitudes such as this, I propose the following upgrades to warrior only equipment.<br>
<br>
1. All Velious warrior breastplates should now have as a right click effect the spell &quot;Rallos's Protection of War&quot;, which is a 200 HP group buff, recommended level: 60.<br>
<br>
2. New Luclin Legs should drop which are warrior only, which have a right click heal over time called &quot;Cleansing of Battle&quot; which is a 640 point heal spell over 24 seconds with a 3.5 second cast time.<br>
<br>
3. New SoL Shoulders with a Right Click &quot;Refreshing Wave of Tallon&quot; which is a 590 point group heal spell.<br>
<br>
4. A Range Slot item with unlimited charges of &quot;Restoration&quot; a 75% res spell.<br>
<br>
5. Of course, can't forget Arms with a right click 540 point heal spell.<br>
<br>
6. Finally, gloves with instant cast root spell.<br>
<br>
Now, Paladins shouldn't feel threatened by this as after all, we have MUCH lower skills in channelling, Alteration, and Abjuration.   We wouldn't be able to cast most of these in combat, since our channelling is so low, and they're not as effective as your spells, but they should be really close, because really, Paladins shouldn't be able to control the market on melee who can heal and buff and root.  We wouldn't be as good as you, but heck, that's ok, we only need to be about 90% as good as you anyhow.<br>
